comment: If two functions on a base topology ` J ` make the same identifications in order to create quotient spaces ` J qTop F ` and ` J qTop G ` , then not only are ` J qTop F ` and ` J qTop G ` homeomorphic, but there is a unique homeomorphism that makes the diagram commute.
